                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d448">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2531/266: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Frost</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-03-04T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >March 4, 1938—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:17 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>30. Department’s 17, February 14, 6 p.m. Foreign Office states it will begin
                    conversations with Embassy on trade agreement early next week, having its
                    proposals now at last rough drafted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Frost</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
